No longer an 'invisible man': #WestPoint to name new $186million #cadet barracks after black #graduate who was shunned by the entire #university... but went on to become the #first black #general of the #AirForce
By #AnnetaKonstantinides For #Dailymail.com and #AssociatedPress
17:25 EDT 10 May 2015, updated 17:42 EDT 10 May 2015

#BenjaminODavisJr. was the only black cadet at the #academy in 1932
He had no roommates or friends and was rarely even spoken to 
But Davis became one of the academy's most #accomplished graduates
He commanded the all-black #TuskegeeAirmen during #WorldWarII 
Davis retired a three-star general in 1970, was awarded a fourth in 1998 
Benjamin O. Davis Jr. was the only black cadet when he entered West Point in 1932. 
Davis spent his four years at the #military academy shunned, with no roommates or friends, in an experience he later said made him feel like 'an #invisible #man'. Now the university wants to #honor the man who went on to become one of its most accomplished graduates by naming a new $186m cadet barracks after Davis.

Previous graduates who have received the rare #privilege include #President #DwightDEisenhower and #fivestargeneral #DouglasMacArthur. 
But Davis proved he was much more than an 'invisible man' long before this honor came along. 
Davis, who passed away in 2002 at age 89, became the first black general of the Air Force. 
He commanded the all-black #332nd Fighter group, also known as the Tuskegee Airmen and the #RedTails, during World War II. 
They were the first #AfricanAmerican military #aviators in the #UnitedStatesArmedForces.

#Aisha was born in #Adamawa State on February 17, 1971.
She is the daughter of a #civil #engineer (her father) and a direct descendant of the #Ankali family. It’s one of the most popular lineages in the #Northern #Nigeria, well-renowned for their farming and textile industry dominance.
She also happens to be the grand-daughter of Nigeria’s first Minister of Defence, #Mohammadu #Ribadu.
Aisha is a graduate of the #Ahmadu #Bello #University (ABU) with a Bachelor’s degree in Public Administration. She also has a master’s degree in International Affairs and Strategic Studies from the #Nigerian #Defence #Academy (NDA), Kaduna.
Professionally, she was the Founder/Managing Director, Hanzy Beauty Institute, a successful beauty salon franchise in #Kaduna and #Abuja.
Her enterprise did quite well, supported by the brilliant woman’s keen business sense and training in Cosmetology and Beauty from the Academy Esthetique Beauty Institute of #France.
 She is an active advocate of women’s rights in Nigeria. In the past, her work has involved a proposed legislation against early marriage, meetings with the mothers of the abducted #Chibok #Girls and a stance against sex trafficking.
Aisha got married to #President #Buhari in December 1989. The two have ten children together – five biological and five from Buhari’s first marriage to Hajiya Safinatu (nee Yusuf) Buhari.
